        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Receipt for two notes. Commerce.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>I <persName>Joseph H Polly Sheriff of <placeName>Austin's Colony</placeName></persName> do hereby Certify
that I have this day recd from <persName>Stephen F. Austin</persName> two notes one
drawn by <persName>J H Bell</persName> in favor of <persName>Mr James Gains</persName> or order for forty
eight dollars and 25 cts to be paid in hogs at the rate of the <placeName>country</placeName>
and dated <date when="1827-04-25">25th April 1824</date>. and the other drawn by <persName>Wm W Little
</persName>payable to <persName>J H. Bell</persName> for sixty dollars to be discharged in a good
young mule, should one Mule not discharge the debt the balance to
be paid in Corn or Hogs at the choice of the holder the first of
said Notes payable in <date n="11-xx-1827">Novemr</date>" of the same year and the other in
<date n="10-xx-1827">October</date>&#8212;the said notes having been attached from the possession
of said <persName>Austin </persName>as the <placeName>property of <persName>James Gains</persName> </placeName>by an order of the
<persName>Alcalde of the Dist of <placeName>Sanfelipe de Austin</placeName></persName> under date of <date when="1827-04-27">24th April
1827</date> on the petition of <persName>Wm Prator</persName>.</p>

<p><placeName>Sn Felipe de Austin</placeName><date when="1827-04-28"> 28 April 1827   </date>             <persName>J H Polley. Const.</persName></p>


        </div1>
